title: The Glory of Watercolour
description:
The Glory of Watercolour. The Royal Watercolour Society Diploma Collection
David and Charles Publishers | 1987 English | 200 pages | PDF | 30 MB

The Bankside Gallery, London, is the home of the Royal Watercolour Society (RWS) which was founded in 1804. Since its inauguration the RWS has received a gift of a painting from virtually every major British watercolour painter This unique collection forms the basis. from which the 135 colour illustrations have been selected
